    thinking: "**Confirming Initial Build**\n\nI\'ve successfully created the modular subcomponents! The critical files, including `/src/types.ts`, `/src/components/TacticalMap.tsx`, `/src/components/IntelStream.tsx`, `/src/components/TriagePanel.tsx`, and `/src/components/ShelterLocator.tsx`, are now in place. These form the fundamental building blocks of the tactical application, which is a great start.\n\n\n**Designing the Dashboard**\n\nI\'m now focused on constructing the master `/src/App.tsx` layout. I\'m aiming for a NERV-inspired geospatial command center, starting with a grid-snapped design. I\'ve broken down the header elements: title with a live stream tag, a ticking time display, sector selector, and system status indicator. The sidebar will include navigation options like GEOSPATIAL, INTEL_STREAM, RESOURCE_LOCATOR, MULTI_AGENT_AI, and SIMULATION. I\'m carefully considering how to represent the NERV aesthetic! I\'m also planning to replace the `/src/App.tsx` file itself.\n\n\n**Refining Bento Layout**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the dashboard\'s design, specifically the \"bento grid\" layout. I\'ve decided this consolidated, single-screen view will be the default, perfectly capturing the desired aesthetic. I\'m mapping the exact layout, starting with the side navigation panel in Column 1, followed by the top bar elements, and then the lower action buttons. Clicking on sidebar navigation will focus a detail or expand a popup. The bottom buttons will include EVAC, LOGS, and LOGOUT.\n\n\n**Mapping Bento Components**\n\nI\'m now deep in the main grid\'s structure. Column 2 is finalized with its components. I\'ve got the header at the top, followed by the bento-style blocks. I\'m especially excited about the `SIMULATION_CONTROLS` card, which I\'ll float over the `TACTICAL_MAP_VIEW`, which is a large left-center block! The right-center side will now house the `INTEL_STREAM` at the top and the combined `TriagePanel`, which handles triage and resource coordination. Finally, I\'ve got the `SHELTER_&_RESOURCE_LOCATOR` and status bar at the bottom.\n\n\n**Implementing State Logic**\n\nI\'m now integrating dynamic state management into `/src/App.tsx`. I\'ve outlined the core states: `activeAlert`, `selectedShelterId`, `feed`, `shelters`, `satelliteImage`, `triageStatus`, and `activeSector`. I\'m starting with a minimal, simulated disaster event to initialize everything and ensure the application boots. Next, I\'ll integrate server synchronization by fetching initial data from `/api/shelters` and `/api/intel`, followed by connecting to the SSE stream at `/api/stream`.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will replace the main `src/App.tsx` file to implement the comprehensive tactical command center dashboard layout, coordinating SSE real-time streaming, map and locator overlays, flashing alarm siren states, sector selectors, and full-screen evacuation mode."
