sualizing Landmasses**\n\nI\'m now visualizing the landmasses, focusing on a water-colored background and then drawing the land. I\'m experimenting with a large polygon for landmasses, carefully outlining the West/North/East land features, starting from the bottom-left and going up the coast, considering coordinates for Kanagawa, Yokohama, Kawasaki, Haneda Airport, and the Sumida/Arakawa River mouths, including detours for rivers and islands.\n\n\n**Constructing Coastline Contours**\n\nI\'m finalizing the landmass outlines with a single path, starting coordinates and completing the polygon. I am now experimenting with styling: dark slate for dark mode, light cream for light mode. The water background will be styled in a contrasting color. I have detailed a full outline. I am considering the color styling, which will produce a nice, realistic, and elegant map.\n\nI am also considering adding the Rainbow Bridge in Tokyo.\n\n\n**Adding Iconic Features**\n\nI am now focusing on adding specific iconic landmarks. I\'ve mapped the locations for the Rainbow Bridge, Haneda Airport\'s runways, the Tokyo Bay Aqualine, and the Tokyo Tower. I also want to include the Tokyo Skytree, and Mount Fuji in the direction of South-West. I have also thought of adding labels for the Boso and Miura Peninsulas. Finally, I\'m thinking of creating interactive ripple waves for active alerts.\n\n\n"
