    modified_response: "I have successfully integrated the **Japan Tactical Disaster Center (JTDC)** branding and implemented dynamic Light/Dark theme capabilities across the entire user interface.\n\n### Summary of Completed Upgrades\n\n*   **Tactical Branding Update**:\n    *   Renamed NERV operational markers and command headers to **Japan Tactical Disaster Center (JTDC)**.\n    *   Updated default disaster logs, evac siren dialogues, footers, and sidebar coordinates to reference **JTDC Command Units**.\n*   **Dynamic Theme Toggle**:\n    *   Added a tactile **LIGHT_MODE / DARK_MODE** switch button in the top system bar.\n    *   Styled all panels, tables, and buttons to automatically transition with clean CSS transitions between the classic retro dark matrix mode and a high-contrast editorial light theme.\n*   **Intuitive Map Interactions**:\n    *   Enabled **click-to-simulate** epicenter placement: clicking anywhere on the map triggers an instant seismic calculation at those precise latitude/longitude coordinates.\n    *   Styled map widgets\342\200\224including Umihotaru PA, Tokyo Tower, Skytree, Haneda runways, and routing overlay boxes\342\200\224to remain legible in both themes.\n*   **Sub-Component Polish**:\n    *   **Simulation Ingestion**: Styled the satellite drag-and-drop container, scenario triggers, and prompt inputs for maximum light-mode readability.\n    *   **Shelter Locator**: Adjusted the occupancy block meters and safe flag badges (`EQ`, `TS`, `FL`) to render with high color-contrast on light backgrounds.\n    *   **Intel Stream & Triage reasoning**: Upgraded console log feeds and SMS draft broadcasts to dynamically change background contrasts without losing active telemetry."
    thinking_duration {
